<div class="container-fluid welcome-header">
  <!-- <h1>Learn Together</h1> -->
  <div class="header-logo">
    <%= image_tag("learn_together_stack.png") %>
  </div>

  <div class="section-subtitle">
  <p>Because learning to code alone is never easy</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container-fluid bg-1 text-center">
  <% @topics.each do |topic| %>
    <div class="col-xs-3">
      <%= link_to topic_path(topic) do %>
        <div class="thumbnail <%= topic.name %>">
          <div class="thumbnail-header">
            <div class="topic-img"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="caption">
            <h4 class="thumb-title"><%= topic.name %></h4>
            <p class="thumb-text"><%= topic.num_of_resources%> resources</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>  
  <% end %>  
</div>


<div class="container-fluid bg-grey text-center">
  <h3>What is Learn Together all about?</h3>
  <div class="section-subtitle">
    <p>I'm currently learning to become a Fullstack Web Developer, enrolled as an online student at Flatiron School to help me get there.  What I've learned about the Tech Industry is that it's a culture.  A helpful community with vast amounts of knowlegde and wisdom.  If you're anything like me, you need all the help you can get.  I find myself constantly bookmarking sites and reaching out on slack channels or looking back at previous conversations where I think I might have seen someone talk about a certain error I'm getting, or a simpler way to write the code I want. </p>
    <p>The goal of this App is to allow students to share additional resources they found helpful as they were going through one of the 8 topics we learn.  Simply name the resource and add the link and it'll be available to see on the respective topic page.  Let's learn together...happy coding!  </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container-fluid text-center ">
  <h2>Tips</h2>
</div>

<div class="section-subtitle">
  <p>A few things to remember as you're learning to code . . .</p>
  
  <div class="row text-center">
    <div class="col-sm-4">
      <div class="thumbnail-2">
        <%= image_tag("rome2.jpeg", :alt => "rome2") %>
        <p>Rome wasn't built in a day</p>
      </div>
    </div>

